<PubmedArticle><MedlineCitation Status="PubMed-not-MEDLINE" Owner="NLM"><PMID Version="1">41442347</PMID><DateRevised><Year>2025</Year><Month>12</Month><Day>24</Day></DateRevised><Article PubModel="Print"><Journal><ISSN IssnType="Electronic">1539-4794</ISSN><JournalIssue CitedMedium="Internet"><Volume>51</Volume><Issue>1</Issue><PubDate><Year>2026</Year><Month>Jan</Month><Day>01</Day></PubDate></JournalIssue><Title>Optics letters</Title><ISOAbbreviation>Opt Lett</ISOAbbreviation></Journal><ArticleTitle>Soliton self-frequency shift in hollow-core fiber for bright femtosecond radiation tunable across the short-wavelength infrared.</ArticleTitle><Pagination><StartPage>33</StartPage><EndPage>36</EndPage><MedlinePgn>33-36</MedlinePgn></Pagination><ELocationID EIdType="doi" ValidYN="Y">10.1364/OL.583522</ELocationID><Abstract><AbstractText>We report a fiber-based source of femtosecond radiation that is spectrally tunable in the short-wavelength infrared region, delivering average powers at the multi-watt level. The system utilizes self-soliton frequency shifting in a hydrogen-filled hollow-core fiber, producing pulse trains at 1.1&#x2009;MHz with integrated relative intensity noise below 0.3% and a polarization extinction ratio of 30&#x2009;dB. This source constitutes an efficient and valid fiber-based alternative to optical parametric amplifiers for a variety of applications, including THz generation, multiphoton imaging, and high-harmonic generation.</AbstractText></Abstract><AuthorList CompleteYN="Y"><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Lippl</LastName><ForeName>Markus</ForeName><Initials>M</Initials></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Butryn</LastName><ForeName>Martin</ForeName><Initials>M</Initials></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Joly</LastName><ForeName>Nicolas Y</ForeName><Initials>NY</Initials></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Tani</LastName><ForeName>Francesco</ForeName><Initials>F</Initials></Author></AuthorList><Language>eng</Language><PublicationTypeList><PublicationType UI="D016428">Journal Article</PublicationType></PublicationTypeList></Article><MedlineJournalInfo><Country>United States</Country><MedlineTA>Opt Lett</MedlineTA><NlmUniqueID>7708433</NlmUniqueID><ISSNLinking>0146-9592</ISSNLinking></MedlineJournalInfo><CitationSubset>IM</CitationSubset></MedlineCitation><PubmedData><History><PubMedPubDate PubStatus="medline"><Year>2025</Year><Month>12</Month><Day>24</Day><Hour>19</Hour><Minute>34</Minute></PubMedPubDate><PubMedPubDate PubStatus="pubmed"><Year>2025</Year><Month>12</Month><Day>24</Day><Hour>19</Hour><Minute>33</Minute></PubMedPubDate><PubMedPubDate PubStatus="entrez"><Year>2025</Year><Month>12</Month><Day>24</Day><Hour>13</Hour><Minute>3</Minute></PubMedPubDate></History><PublicationStatus>ppublish</PublicationStatus><ArticleIdList><ArticleId IdType="pubmed">41442347</ArticleId><ArticleId IdType="doi">10.1364/OL.583522</ArticleId><ArticleId IdType="pii">584931</ArticleId></ArticleIdList></PubmedData></PubmedArticle></PubmedArticleSet>